WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.400 --> 00:00:05.920
have you ever imagined being able to view

00:00:05.920 --> 00:00:08.499
things like a superhero? wouldn't it be

00:00:08.499 --> 00:00:10.509
amazing to be able to see details of

00:00:10.509 --> 00:00:11.950
things right in front of you that you

00:00:11.950 --> 00:00:13.539
didn't even know existed?

00:00:13.539 --> 00:00:16.539
well now you can with the Carson X-View.

00:00:16.539 --> 00:00:19.689
Carson  X-View monocular allows you to focus on

00:00:19.689 --> 00:00:23.320
things far away or extremely close. most

00:00:23.320 --> 00:00:24.910
monoculars have a close focus of

00:00:24.910 --> 00:00:27.429
8 to 10 feet, while the  X-View allows you to focus

00:00:27.429 --> 00:00:30.880
up to 18 inches away from the lens. using

00:00:30.880 --> 00:00:32.740
the  X-View is like walking around with a

00:00:32.740 --> 00:00:34.540
high-powered microscope right in your

00:00:34.540 --> 00:00:37.510
hand. explore the little things in the

00:00:37.510 --> 00:00:40.000
world, and examine butterflies, small

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:43.930
plant pests, ant colonies, brushstrokes

00:00:43.930 --> 00:00:45.610
on paintings and more.

00:00:45.610 --> 00:00:48.610
the possibilities are endless. use the

00:00:48.610 --> 00:00:50.890
X-View to explore your universe. it's

00:00:50.890 --> 00:00:52.540
amazing to see things up close that you

00:00:52.540 --> 00:00:53.620
never knew existed.

00:00:53.620 --> 00:00:56.379
the X-View can also be used as a regular

00:00:56.379 --> 00:00:57.579
monocular for viewing

00:00:57.579 --> 00:00:59.530
objects in the distance.

00:00:59.530 --> 00:01:01.480
the X-View is great to bring along when

00:01:01.480 --> 00:01:03.760
hiking, boating,

00:01:03.760 --> 00:01:07.240
bird watching, hunting and more. it's also

00:01:07.240 --> 00:01:09.759
great for bringing to ball games. the  X-View

00:01:09.759 --> 00:01:11.950
is also a great tool for people with macular

00:01:11.950 --> 00:01:14.290
degeneration for the visually impaired.

00:01:14.290 --> 00:01:16.090
it also works great on TVs and other

00:01:16.090 --> 00:01:19.210
objects too. the X-View features 2 focusing

00:01:19.210 --> 00:01:21.940
mechanisms. when viewing objects at a

00:01:21.940 --> 00:01:24.220
distance turn the large focus wheel until

00:01:24.220 --> 00:01:26.350
the objective lens is at the inward most

00:01:26.350 --> 00:01:29.229
position. once this is done, focusing is

00:01:29.229 --> 00:01:31.060
accomplished by turning the small focus

00:01:31.060 --> 00:01:32.659
wheel closest to the eye.

00:01:32.659 --> 00:01:34.819
when viewing objects at a close-range

00:01:34.819 --> 00:01:36.799
focusing is accomplished by turning the

00:01:36.799 --> 00:01:38.420
large focus wheel closest to the

00:01:38.420 --> 00:01:41.149
objective lens of the monocular. turning this

00:01:41.149 --> 00:01:43.399
focus wheel extend the objective lens outward.

00:01:43.399 --> 00:01:46.549
the X-View is fitted with a twisting eye cup

00:01:46.549 --> 00:01:48.740
which eliminates extraneous light and

00:01:48.740 --> 00:01:50.479
provides users with eyeglasses an

00:01:50.479 --> 00:01:52.729
improved field of view. the X-View is

00:01:52.729 --> 00:01:55.039
equipt with the standard tripod and

00:01:55.039 --> 00:01:56.750
can be attached to most tripods for

00:01:56.750 --> 00:01:59.390
easy hands-free use. whether you use it

00:01:59.390 --> 00:02:00.890
to view objects off in the distance or

00:02:00.890 --> 00:02:02.539
right in front of you,

00:02:02.539 --> 00:02:04.609
the X-View is the perfect tool to enhance your

00:02:04.609 --> 00:02:10.090
viewing experience

